actor.name: Elevator
actor.description: This agent is responsible for moving the passengers among the floors.

actor.name: Passenger
actor.description: This agent boards in or debark from the elevator, so he can be transported from one floor to another.

useCase.name: Move to lower floor
useCase.description: The agent elevator moves from the origin floor to the destination floor, which is immediately down.

definition.invariants: - the elevator door remains closed; - the elevator load doesn't change.

useCase.name: Board
useCase.description: The agent passenger boards in an elevator at his origin floor.

definition.postcondition: - the passenger is inside the elevator; - the elevator load increases.
definition.invariants: - the passenger and the elevator remain at the same floor.

useCase.name: Debark
useCase.description: The agent passenger debarks from the elevator at his destination floor.

useCase.name: Move to upper floor
useCase.description: The agent elevator moves from the origin floor to the destination floor, which is immediately up.

definition.postcondition: - the elevator is at the destination floor, i. e., it has moved one floor up.
definition.invariants: - the elevator door remains closed; - the elevator load doesn't change.

state.name: Passenger waiting for an elevator
state.condition: p.boarded = false and p.served = false and p.inside = null

state.name: Passenger boarded in an elevator
state.condition: p.boarded = true and p.served = false and p.inside = e

state.name: Passenger served
state.condition: p.boarded = false and p.served = true and p.inside = null

problem.name: one elevator six floors five passengers
